reviews.headline: Better than expected!
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] At first glance, I thought the shade wouldn't work for me. I received shade 40 - all the tea which appears like a reddish brown. I thought it would be too dark for me. For reference, I have pretty fair skin with rosy hues. When opening the package, I also thought the applicator was huge and thought it would make a mess when trying to apply. Upon application, I noticed that the applicator actually helps to cup your lip to apply the product easier and more evenly. I also noticed that the gloss appears much lighter and less pigmented than it does in the tube - which worked for me. It kind of just enhanced my naturally pink lips - leaving a little light red hue. The product felt very hydrating & nourishing - and not drying at all. The only thing I'm kind of iffy on is the minty smell/feel - which can sometimes be overpowering or irritating to the skin surrounding the lips. Other than that, I think it's a good every day use product -- to add some shine, and hydration. This is great to be used by itself or with a lip liner or over a matter lipstick! 
* I recieved this product for free in exchange for my honest review!

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have to tell you about this new lip gloss-Lanc√¥me JuicyTreat 20% Squalane 3D Juicy Shine Oil-In-Gloss in the shade 33 Idole Nude. It is so good, I'm actually obsessed.

First of all, the packaging is totally luxe‚Äîexactly what you'd expect from Lanc√¥me. It feels high-end the moment you pull it out of your bag. And the applicator? Perfection. It's plush, has the perfect shape to hug your lips just right, and it picks up just the right amount of product. No mess, no fuss‚Äîjust a smooth, even swipe.

Now the scent is what really surprised me‚Äîit's like this yummy minty cookie vibe. Sweet and refreshing without being overpowering, and it gives you that little zing on your lips right after you apply. It's such a cool, tingly sensation‚Äîsuper refreshing and makes your lips feel instantly awake and pampered.

The shade 33 Idole Nude is chef's kiss‚Äîa gorgeous, universally flattering nude with a hint of peachy-pink warmth that makes your lips look so juicy and healthy. But honestly, the color range in general is stunning. There's something for everyone‚Äîsoft pinks, bold berries, deep bronzes. Each one has this gorgeous, dimensional shine that makes your lips look fuller and smoother, thanks to that 3D finish.

It's packed with 20% squalane, so it actually hydrates while you wear it. No stickiness at all‚Äîjust this cushiony, silky feel that wears like a balm but looks like glass. It lasts surprisingly well for a gloss, too. I don't feel like I'm constantly reapplying, and my lips always feel better after wearing it, which is rare for a gloss.

Seriously, if you're looking for a gloss that feels amazing, looks beautiful, and smells good enough to eat, this one is IT. I'm already eyeing a couple more shades. You've gotta try it!
faceoff_positive.headline: Juicy and glossy and long lasting!!!!

faceoff_negative.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I am absolutely obsessed the the Lancome LIP IDOLE JUICY TREAT Oil-In-Gloss. The packaging is very beautiful and lux. It looks and feels very expensive. The smell of the berry was absolutely beautiful. The gloss is beyond hydrating and looks and feels great on the lips. The two things I didn't like were the applicator and the overall price point for the gloss. Another thought, while I loved this color I also feel like the range of colors for my skin color lack. I personally prefer a darker shade that matches my natural lip. This color was perfect but it looks like the only one I'd actually use. Overall I would recommend this product but I would only purchase this shade again. Over all for shade range, price, and applicator I give it a good 3/5 star rating.
faceoff_negative.headline: Beautiful and Hydrating
